creator: Aesop
description:
LibriVox recording of Celebration of Dialects and Accents, Vol 2. by Aesop. (Translated by George Fyler Townsend.)

Read in English by Linda Jenner; Kris Moore; Julia Niedermaier; Ernst Pattynama; Simon Evers; Claudia Salto; Rebecca Braunert-Plunkett; Maria Kasper; Diana Majlinger; Jason Mills; Bill Mosley; Nicholas James Bridgewater; Steve Lawrence; Ryan Bradburn; Malone; CaprishaPage; Sarah Holtz; sdaeley17; Greg Giordano; Pam Castille

A celebration of all the wonderful dialects and accents found within the Librivox community! The goal being to record a 'phonetically relevant' text by as many volunteers as possible, and make this dialect/accent 'database' available to the world, by releasing the recordings into the public domain. - Summary by Délibáb)

For further information, including links to online text, reader information, RSS feeds, CD cover or other formats (if available), please go to the LibriVox catalog page for this recording.

For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org.

M4B Format Available
